For reference, Chrome's JSON object exhibits the behavior that is being asked for.
e.g. (in console)

    m = {};
    m[22] = "foo";
    m[33] = "bar";
    JSON.stringify(m); // -> {"22":"foo","33":"bar"}
    k = [1,2];
    m[k] = "array";
    JSON.stringify(m); // -> {"22":"foo","33":"bar","1,2":"array"}
